text: Laia Sin Frau (born 3 May 2003) is an Andorran footballer who plays as a midfielder for Andorran-based Spanish Women's First Division of Catalonia club ENFAF and the Andorra women's national team. ==International career== Sin capped for Andorra at senior level in a 1–2 friendly loss to Luxembourg in June 2019. ==References== Category:2003 births Category:Living people Category:Women's association football midfielders Category:Andorran women's footballers Category:Andorra women's international footballers
